[[Afaylu:Ayatul Kursi by AbdurRahman Al Sudais.wav|thumb|''Ayat Alkursi'' s yils n limam [[Ɛabdurrahman Al Sudays]].]]'''Ayat Alkursi''' (s [[Tutlayt Taɛrabt|taɛrabt]]: آية الكرسي, <small>Taɣarast n tiɣri<abbr>.</abbr></small> ''’āyat al-kursī''‎) tga laya tis-255 ɣ ssuṛa nɣ [[Takṭṭumt n tfunast|tkṭṭumt n tfunast]] ɣ [[Lqʷran|Lqqʷran]] lli d isggiz rbbi f urqqas nns [[Muḥammad]] {{saw}} taẓallit n rbbi fllas ɣ yiḍ n Lqadr ɣ wayyur n Rmḍan, ilkm uṭṭun n tassuṛin nns 114. Tga laya ad yat zɣ layat lli llanin ɣ tassurin n udlis n ṛbbi. Laya ad ar tettinni mas iga rbbi yan, ur illi mad t irwasn.<ref> [https://quran.com/2/255?translations=131 "Surat Al Baqara"] . ''quran.com''. Retrieved 16 October2020.</ref> Ilkm wuṭṭun n tguriwin nns 50, ku yat gi-s lbaṛaka , lliɣ tggiz laya ad rwln ibalisn, inta (ibda) umzwaru n tassuṛt s yism n rbbi «''بسم الله»'' ,d umggaru nns s yism nns «''العلي العظيم»''.<ref>Abdullah Yusuf Ali (1983) <small>[First published 1934]</small>. ''The Holy Qur'ān: Text, Translation and Commentary''. Brentwood, Maryland: Amana Corp. pp. 102–103.</ref>

Laya ad tga yat laya bahra istawhman dar [[Lislam|imslmn]] d tugt nnsn ḥsan-tt s wul nnsn.<ref>Seyyed Hossein Nasr, ed. (2018). ''The Study Quran''. HarperCollins Publishers. p. 110.</ref>

